    internalDebates:[
      'Whether the umbrella names a philosophically meaningful family or mainly an institutional contrast produced by curricula, languages, and professional networks.',
      'Whether historical development can be narrated without imposing teleology, Eurocentrism, or retrospective necessity on conflict and suffering.',
      'Whether phenomenology should begin from transcendental consciousness, being-in-the-world, embodied perception, social situation, or ethical relation.',
      'How freedom and responsibility persist under material constraint, embodied habit, ideology, normalization, and socially formed subjectivity.',
      'Whether hermeneutic dialogue can criticize domination or relies too heavily on traditions and communicative conditions already shaped by power.',
      'Whether social critique should center class and production, recognition and communication, dispersed normalization, colonial history, gender, race, or their interaction.',
      'Whether genealogy and deconstruction can justify normative criticism or must borrow standards they unsettle.',
      'How structure, language, discourse, embodied agency, and historical transformation relate without making one explanatory level absolute.',
      'Whether universal claims about reason and emancipation can be reconstructed inclusively or should be treated with genealogical suspicion.',
      'How philosophical style, conceptual invention, historical archive, description, formal argument, and empirical inquiry should share intellectual authority.'
    ],
    rivalPositions:['analytic-philosophy','german-idealism','phenomenology','existentialism','political-philosophy','philosophy-of-language','philosophy-of-mind','feminist-philosophy','pragmatism'],
    modernRelevanceDetailed:[
      'Phenomenology clarifies how digital devices, medicine, disability, architecture, and social environments reorganize embodiment, attention, time, and practical possibility.',
      'Hermeneutics examines how inherited languages, archives, media, translation, and automated summaries shape public understanding and historical memory.',
      'Marxist and critical-theory approaches connect platform ownership, labor, commodification, surveillance, and culture to wider structures of political economy.',
      'Genealogy tests the apparent naturalness of classifications involving normality, risk, intelligence, sexuality, citizenship, health, and deviance.',
      'Feminist and queer revisions show how norms are embodied and institutional while remaining historically variable and politically contestable.',
      'Critical theories of race and colonial history expose exclusions inside supposedly universal accounts of subjectivity, reason, development, and public membership.',
      'Continental philosophy of technology asks how tools disclose worlds and form subjects instead of treating technology as a neutral collection of devices.',
      'Ecological work draws on materialism, phenomenology, and critical theory to connect lived environments with production, unequal vulnerability, and more-than-human relations.'
    ],
    misconceptionsDetailed:[
      'Continental philosophy is a retrospective institutional umbrella, not one school, doctrine, method, political program, or self-chosen identity shared by all included thinkers.',
      'It is not defined merely as non-analytic philosophy, and geography cannot sort the two traditions reliably.',
      'Its thinkers do not uniformly reject clarity, logic, science, truth, or argument; they disagree about what rigor requires and use many forms of evidence and reasoning.',
      'Phenomenology is not casual introspection, existentialism is not nihilism, and hermeneutics is not permission to impose any interpretation.',
      'Marxism, critical theory, structuralism, post-structuralism, genealogy, and deconstruction are not interchangeable names for social criticism.',
      'Genealogy does not refute a belief solely by revealing a contingent origin, and Foucault’s account of power does not make resistance or warranted truth claims impossible.',
      'Deconstruction does not destroy a text or prove that language is meaningless; it analyzes dependencies and exclusions within claims to stable meaning.',
      'Gender performativity does not mean gender is a theatrical role freely selected by an unconstrained individual.',
      'Difficulty can sometimes serve conceptual or stylistic purposes, but difficulty itself neither proves depth nor excuses a failed argument.',
      'Major figures did not all accept the “continental” label, and responsible history must preserve self-identification, chronology, political complicity, and movement-specific differences.'
    ],
